{
  "title": "Ease",
  "description": "Standard Robert Penner easing functions as static methods. Each function accepts a normalized time `t` in [0, 1] and returns a value that equals 0 at t=0 and 1 at t=1 (overshoot functions like back/elastic may exceed that range between the endpoints). Usage: `Ease.cubicOut`, `Ease.bounceIn`, etc. Note: only scalar numeric properties are supported in v1. Vector, Color, and Matrix interpolation are out of scope.",
  "symbol": "Ease",
  "kind": "class",
